#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.42:0.2"
msgid "5. Cūḷavagga "
msgstr "5. The Lesser Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Tiṭhānasutta "
msgstr "42. Three Grounds "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.42:1.1"
msgid "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, ṭhānehi saddho pasanno veditabbo. "
msgstr "“There are three grounds, mendicants, by which a person with faith and confidence can be known. "

msgctxt "an3.42:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.42:1.3"
msgid "Sīlavantānaṃ dassanakāmo hoti, saddhammaṃ sotukāmo hoti, vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato. "
msgstr "They like to see ethical people. They like to hear the true teaching. And they live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

# NOTE: Notice that the usual -ti is omitted here.
msgctxt "an3.42:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi ṭhānehi saddho pasanno veditabbo. "
msgstr "These are the three grounds by which a person with faith and confidence can be known. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.42:2.1"
msgid "Dassanakāmo sīlavataṃ, "
msgstr "They like to see ethical people; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.2"
msgid "saddhammaṃ sotumicchati; "
msgstr "they want to hear the true teaching; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.3"
msgid "Vinaye maccheramalaṃ, "
msgstr "they’ve driven out the stain of stinginess: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.4"
msgid "sa ve saddhoti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "that’s who’s called a person of faith.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.42:2.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
